  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is either <math alttext=\"negative 30\"><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn>\n</math> or <math alttext=\"30\"><mn>30</mn>\n</math>. Adding <math alttext=\"7\"><mn>7</mn>\n</math> to each side of the given equation yields <math alttext=\"left parenthesis d minus 30 right parenthesis left parenthesis d plus 30 right parenthesis equals 0\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>30</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. Since a product of two factors is equal to <math alttext=\"0\"><mn>0</mn>\n</math> if and only if at least one of the factors is <math alttext=\"0\"><mn>0</mn>\n</math>, either <math alttext=\"d minus 30 equals 0\"><mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi>d</mi>\n<mo>-</mo>\n<mn>30</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math> or <math alttext=\"d plus 30 equals 0\"><mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi>d</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>30</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Adding <math alttext=\"30\"><mn>30</mn>\n</math> to each side of the equation <math alttext=\"d minus 30 equals 0\"><mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi>d</mi>\n<mo>-</mo>\n<mn>30</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math> yields <math alttext=\"d equals 30\"><mrow>\n<mi>d</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>30</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Subtracting <math alttext=\"30\"><mn>30</mn>\n</math> from each side of the equation <math alttext=\"d plus 30 equals 0\"><mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi>d</mi>\n<mo>+</mo>\n<mn>30</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math> yields <math alttext=\"d equals negative 30\"><mrow>\n<mi>d</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Therefore, the solutions to the given equation are <math alttext=\"negative 30\"><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn>\n</math> and <math alttext=\"30\"><mn>30</mn>\n</math>. Note that -30 and 30 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer.</p>",
